Task 3 – Coding and Collaboration Platforms
Part A – Coding Practice: HackerRank
Platform Used: HackerRank (hackerrank.com)
I created an account on HackerRank and completed the "Solve Me First" challenge under the Problem Solving section. This is HackerRank's introductory challenge: given two integers, write a function that returns their sum.
What I did:

Selected Python 3 as my language.
Read the problem statement, which follows HackerRank's standard format: Input Format → Constraints → Output Format → Sample Input/Output.
Wrote the solution, tested against the sample cases, and submitted.
Result: All test cases passed. Score: 1/1.

Key learning: Even a trivially simple challenge is useful because it teaches the structure of competitive programming problems. Understanding how to read input from stdin and format output correctly is a foundational skill for all subsequent challenges.

